<TITLE> Emdadullah to be grilled further </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 07 (bdnews24.com)--Police took Emdadullah alias Mahbub, a suspected member of the Pakistan-based Islamist terrorist organisation Lashkar-e-Taiba, on a a fresh three-day remand for further interrogation. Metropolitan magistrate Mehedi Hassan Talukder gave the order after Emdadullah was produced to court after four days of remand. Detective Branch of police inspector Mohammed Ashraf Hossain sought to remand him of ten days for further interrogation to arrest the associates of Emdadullah hiding in the country. Emdadullah was arrested by a DB police team at Gabtoli in the capital on Oct 1. He is a suspected member of Harkatul Jihadia Islamia Azadia, a Pakistan-based militant group. He is also the Bangladesh chief of Asif Reza Commando force and member of Lashkar-e-Taiba. Lashkar-e-Taiba was accused of 'Mumbai attack' in November last year. Indian intelligence agencies found Ajmal Amir Kasab's involvement with Laskar-e-Taiba. Kasab is the only attacker who was captured alive during November attack. The militant group is also accused of attacking rail track in Mumbai in 2006. It is also blamed for bomb attack at Diwali festival in New Delhi in 2005. At least 500 people died in three attacks. Emdadullah is a resident of Padmapukur village under Bagda in north Chabbish Pargana in India. He is the son of Ansar ali, alias Abu Ansar. 
